Strapi + PostgreSQL + Java Integration Setup

1. Node Setup

nvm install 20
nvm use 20

http://localhost:1337/admin

2. Create Strapi Project

npx create-strapi-app@latest EC-DATA-Container-new-relic-demo-strapi-cms --quickstart

3. Create new collection type

employee and customer

Employee Collection Fields

| Field Name | Type   | Notes           |
| ---------- | ------ | --------------- |
| employeeid | Number | unique          |
| firstname  | Text   |                 |
| lastname   | Text   |                 |
| position   | Text   |                 |
| hiredate   | Date   |                 |
| salary     | Number | decimal allowed |

Customer Collection Fields

| Field Name | Type   | Notes  |
| ---------- | ------ | ------ |
| customerid | Number | unique |
| firstname  | Text   |        |
| lastname   | Text   |        |
| email      | Email  |        |
| phone      | Text   |        |

Relation field in customer

type: relation
employee

4. Sample Data

employeeid = 101
firstname = John
lastname = Smith
position = Manager
hiredate = 01/01/2024
salary = 120000

customer data:

customerid = 1
firstname = John
lastname = Carter
email = [john@test.com](mailto:john@test.com)
phone = 9991111111
employee = Alice Johnson

5. Relation Table Created by Strapi

Strapi creates relation in separate table:

select * from customers_employee_lnk;

id	customer_id	employee_id
1	1	1
2	2	2

